- Scope notes: In scope, splitting the intake into child stories for sprint cadence and date rules, date-range paging, ticket-assignment behavior during planning, and backlog storage decisions. In scope, preserving the original request and making the dependency order explicit. In scope, treating `BACKLOG-058`, `BACKLOG-059`, and `BACKLOG-060` as the current Sprint 12 delivery slice while `BACKLOG-061` remains deferred until the storage decision is ready. Out of scope, carrying this request as one implementation ticket or choosing a final UI and storage design on the parent card.
