## BACKLOG-068 - Containerize hosted backlog upload and project-pill naming
- Status: Grooming
- Owner: Paula Product
- Requester: current session
- Date added: 2026-04-14
- Updated: 2026-04-14T21:31:57.000Z
- Due Date: 
- Priority: P1
- Effort: 3
- Sprint Assigned: 
- Ready for Implementation?: No
- Tech handoff owner: Unassigned
- Summary: Deliver a first hosted deployment slice that runs in a container with the `codex` package installed and replaces `Open` with markdown backlog upload that stores files locally and exposes them through project pills.
- Outcome / user value: Users can bring a backlog into a hosted instance without local-path setup, then switch between uploaded projects through clean project pills that do not leak filesystem paths.
- Scope notes: In scope, defining the first containerized deployment shape for the hosted app, including the requirement that the runtime image has the `codex` package available for Paula and sprint-run workflows. In scope, replacing the current `Open` action with an upload-first backlog intake flow for markdown files, storing the uploaded file locally on the hosted instance, creating or updating the matching project-pill reference, and showing only the file name stub on project-pill hover instead of the full stored path. In scope, clarifying the minimum upload constraints and duplicate-file handling needed for a safe v1. Out of scope, external object storage, collaborative file libraries, full document management, or exposing raw server filesystem paths in the UI.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] The hosted deployment story defines a containerized runtime for the app and includes the `codex` package as a required part of that runtime.
  - [ ] The primary backlog-entry action for hosted use is an upload flow for markdown backlog files rather than the current path-based `Open` behavior.
  - [ ] Uploading a markdown backlog stores the file locally on the hosted instance and makes it available as a selectable project pill.
  - [ ] Project pills created from uploaded backlogs show a short readable file name stub on hover instead of the full stored path.
  - [ ] The story defines what happens when a user uploads a file whose name conflicts with an already stored project file.
- Dependencies: BACKLOG-045, hosted local-file storage decision, container deployment decision, Paula runtime requirements.
- Links: current session request
- Implementation notes: Original intake preserved in product terms: deploy in a containerised instance with the codex package installed, convert `Open` into markdown upload that stores the file locally and references it in project pills, and show only the markdown file name stub on project-pill mouseover.

## BACKLOG-069 - Add a lightweight user profile switcher
- Status: Grooming
- Owner: Paula Product
