## BACKLOG-060 - Define ticket assignment behavior for dated sprints
- Status: Ready
- Owner: Paula Product
- Requester: current session
- Date added: 2026-04-14
- Updated: 2026-04-14T15:07:20.856Z
- Due Date: 
- Priority: P1
- Effort: 2
- Sprint Assigned: 
- Ready for Implementation?: Yes
- Tech handoff owner: Ben
- Summary: Assign tickets into the dated sprint window currently being planned, with explicit reassignment for unstarted work and protection for started work.
- Outcome / user value: Users can place work into the right dated sprint with less guesswork because the planner makes the active time box and reassignment rules explicit.
- Scope notes: In scope, showing the selected dated sprint window anywhere the planner assigns work, assigning unscheduled tickets directly into that selected window, and asking for explicit confirmation before reassigning an unstarted ticket that already belongs to another sprint. In scope, preserving the existing rule that started work is never moved automatically between sprints. Out of scope, changing backlog schema, auto-rebalancing work across multiple dated sprints, or changing done-story sprint protections.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] The planner shows the currently selected dated sprint context anywhere a user assigns a ticket to that sprint.
  - [ ] Assigning an unscheduled ticket while a dated sprint window is selected writes that sprint assignment to the ticket.
  - [ ] If an unstarted ticket is already assigned to another sprint, the planner asks for explicit confirmation before replacing that assignment.
  - [ ] Tickets in `In Progress`, `Testing`, `Review`, or `Done` are not automatically moved to a different sprint by dated planning actions.
  - [ ] The reassignment flow makes it obvious which sprint the ticket is leaving and which sprint it will enter.
- Dependencies: BACKLOG-058, BACKLOG-059, sprint assignment UI, started-work protection rules.
- Links: current session request
- Implementation notes: Leave blank until the item is `Ready` or in execution

