## BACKLOG-044 - Support core sprint work on mobile
- Status: Ready
- Owner: Paula Product
- Requester: current session
- Date added: 2026-04-14
- Updated: 2026-04-14T13:51:38.000Z
- Due Date: 
- Priority: P1
- Effort: 2
- Sprint Assigned: 
- Ready for Implementation?: Yes
- Tech handoff owner: Ben
- Summary: Deliver a mobile board mode that keeps review, grooming, and sprint-launch actions usable on a phone-sized screen.
- Outcome / user value: Users can review backlog state and kick off sprint work away from a desktop instead of waiting to return to a larger screen.
- Scope notes: In scope, a phone-first layout that switches to one visible lane at a time with tap-selectable lane chips, keeps filters and sprint context reachable without hover, and preserves story-detail access plus sprint actions on a narrow screen. In scope, targeting the smallest coherent workflow at roughly 390px width. Out of scope, full desktop feature parity, tablet-specific polish, or broad visual redesign unrelated to mobile usability.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] At phone width, the board shows one lane at a time and lets users switch lanes through visible tap targets instead of relying on horizontal drag-only discovery.
