## BACKLOG-067 - Submit long chat input without terminal paging trap
- Status: Ready
- Owner: Paula Product
- Requester: current session
- Date added: 2026-04-14
- Updated: 2026-04-14T19:28:52.000Z
- Due Date: 
- Priority: P1
- Effort: 2
- Sprint Assigned: Sprint 11
- Ready for Implementation?: Yes
- Tech handoff owner: Ben
- Summary: Fix long Paula chat submissions that appear to send but remain stuck in terminal paging until the user presses Return again at the bottom of stdin.
- Outcome / user value: Users can trust `Send` and Return for long prompts instead of thinking their message was submitted when it is still waiting in a hidden terminal paging state.
- Scope notes: In scope, making one `Send` or Return action submit one long Paula prompt end to end without forcing the user into the terminal to finish it manually. In scope, handling the long-input path even when the terminal would otherwise paginate or buffer stdin, and making the visible send state match the real submission state. In scope, preserving existing short-message behavior. Out of scope, redesigning the broader Paula chat layout or changing unrelated queue behavior already tracked elsewhere.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] When a user submits a very long prompt from the Paula chat composer, one `Send` or Return action results in one actual prompt submission.
  - [ ] The UI does not show a misleading sending animation when the prompt is still waiting inside terminal paging or another intermediate stdin state.
  - [ ] If long input requires overflow handling, that handling completes within the same send action and does not require the user to switch to the terminal to finish submission manually.
  - [ ] Short prompts continue to submit with the current expected `Send` and Return behavior.
  - [ ] After the long prompt is submitted, the chat shows the same observable post-send behavior as a normal successful submission instead of leaving the message in a half-sent state.
- Dependencies: Paula chat composer, send action state, terminal stdin handoff, long-input handling.
- Links: current session request
- Implementation notes: Original intake preserved verbatim: on very long text input in the chat, pressing Send/return starts the animation but nothing else happens. On switching to the terminal, the stdin needs to be paged through and then it's clear that it has not been submitted. Pressing return at the bottom of the stdin then submits the prompt

